{"tid":871032,"cid":5,"subCid":0,"title":"奶粉全被中國代購掃光 澳洲人哭求：留點給我們孩子","createTime":"2018-10-21T14:59:55.000Z","updateTime":"2018-10-24T01:11:38.000Z","uid":39464,"like":546,"dislike":2,"uniUserReply":96,"replies":[{"pid":"7ba92f5e81e8b0f2162073e63bb7419a41cc18a0","tid":871032,"uid":39464,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-10-21T14:59:55.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"http://img.ltn.com.tw/Upload/liveNews/BigPic/600_phpkM0MOe.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=http%3A%2F%2Fimg.ltn.com.tw%2FUpload%2FliveNews%2FBigPic%2F600_phpkM0MOe.jpg&h=22ecfcab&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<br />\n〔即時新聞／綜合報導〕中國代購商近年瘋狂到澳洲搶購奶粉，導致澳洲奶粉供不應求，當地民眾到超市往往發現，奶粉架上已經空無一物，一名父親迫於無奈，8日甚至還寫信給奶粉公司請求：「拜託你留點奶粉給我們孩子吧！」<br />\n<br />\n據《環球網》報導，由於中國代購商大量搶購澳洲奶粉，導致有許多澳洲寶寶喝不到嬰兒配方奶，許多父母著急得不得了，不是被迫得到很遠的地方買奶粉，就是得先打電話到超市預定，否則到場後肯定撲空，對此，有民眾忍無可忍憤怒的表示，「這是怎麼回事？我們生活在澳洲當地買不到，卻能在超市倉庫裡看到一堆要送往中國的奶粉！」10月8日更有一名父親，直接寫信向奶粉公司請求，「拜託你留點奶粉給我們的孩子吧！」可見澳洲產奶粉熱賣程度。<br />\n<br />\n對此，澳洲連鎖超級市場「Woolworths」表示，先前規定「每人限購2罐」的政策會繼續執行，另一間「Coles」超市也表示，初生嬰兒的配方奶粉只會在服務櫃台出售，防止代購商不斷折返採購，確保有需要的民眾可以買到這些商品。<br />\n<br />\n不過，許多澳洲網友仍對中國代購商入到當地掃購的狀況不滿，表示「中國國產奶粉已完全不值得相信嗎？」、「我們簡直淪為二等公民」、「作為一個母親卻餵不飽自己孩子，令人心碎」、「超市還是有人一箱一箱的搬」、「現在要我們用哭求的方式才能買到奶粉了」。<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"http://img.ltn.com.tw/Upload/liveNews/BigPic/600_phpgrBDyn.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=http%3A%2F%2Fimg.ltn.com.tw%2FUpload%2FliveNews%2FBigPic%2F600_phpgrBDyn.jpg&h=84f189d3&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n澳洲一名父親因為買不到奶粉，乾脆寫信向奶粉公司請求，「拜託你留點奶粉給我們孩子吧！」<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"http://news.ltn.com.tw/news/world/breakingnews/2587692\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=http%3A%2F%2Fnews.ltn.com.tw%2Fnews%2Fworld%2Fbreakingnews%2F2587692&d=XAwIn4HCiavbvNoE0BIO3jOU%2Fspzl0GStOx2So8CiJ8%3D&h=d233e43a\" data-ef-url=\"https://embed.lih.kg/frame?u=http%3A%2F%2Fnews.ltn.com.tw%2Fnews%2Fworld%2Fbreakingnews%2F2587692&h=a71b1bf2\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">http://news.ltn.com.tw/news/world/breakingnews/2587692</a>"},{"pid":"6088abc4b713a72cafa40e7d5dfb813b57e4e048","tid":871032,"uid":102078,"like":765,"dislike":2,"score":763,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-10-21T15:02:35.000Z","msg":"今日香港.今日澳洲<img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/smile.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/hehe.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/smile.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/hehe.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"c7b143c89b5a4134414ceddb9551cb64dae60950","tid":871032,"uid":55592,"like":286,"dislike":1,"score":285,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-10-21T15:02:39.000Z","msg":"中國或成最大贏家"},{"pid":"21b1e9564885856d4670709297908566cbff3e47","tid":871032,"uid":58552,"like":280,"dislike":3,"score":277,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-10-21T15:04:59.000Z","msg":"唔反抗嘅下場"},{"pid":"c7ac6dbae05fdc7d61ee2e20cd11c0f9ca4a4254","tid":871032,"uid":42188,"like":538,"dislike":0,"score":538,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2018-10-21T15:05:29.000Z","msg":"支那：我們沒給錢的？"},{"pid":"b6a3fdacb588c233ec69609cc62ec40624748eb4","tid":871032,"uid":20867,"like":366,"dislike":3,"score":363,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2018-10-21T15:06:52.000Z","msg":"香港人如果身上唔著番件「i am hongkonger not chinese」tee<br />\n出街可能會畀鬼佬打柒<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/@.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/@.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"0077b832e411d073fea383db25acbaefef8ec802","tid":871032,"uid":2114,"like":127,"dislike":0,"score":127,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-10-21T15:09:15.000Z","msg":"同以前香港嘅情況簡直一模一樣 <img src=\"/assets/faces/dog/haha.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"fd44624f21315fad4aa7fe2c18f398f6c3f10f60","tid":871032,"uid":39464,"like":70,"dislike":1,"score":69,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-10-21T15:12:10.000Z","msg":"Ivan Chan, 香港移民?<br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://cdn.mamamia.com.au/wp/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/19095805/facebook-letter.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.mamamia.com.au%2Fwp%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F10%2F19095805%2Ffacebook-letter.jpg&h=47b91252&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<br />\nBaby formula supply remains a serious issue for many parents, and a group is claiming Woolworths&rsquo; latest move has made it even harder for them to feed their children.<br />\n<br />\nSydney father Ivan Chan and two other customers wrote a letter to the supermarket giant &ndash; which they later posted on Woolworths&rsquo; Facebook page &ndash; asking for it to reverse a recent decision.<br />\n<br />\nIn August, Woolworths relaxed its strict infant formula limit from two tins per customer to up to eight tins per customer.<br />\n<br />\nChan and fellow parents said this change has made it much harder for them to find and buy the infant formula they need.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;We are a group of concerned customers who are struggling to obtain baby formula for our babies/toddlers, due to some customers buying eight or more tins of formula,&rdquo; the letter read.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;We have to keep calling stores all over Sydney to feed our children.<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;The problem has become acutely worse since Woolworths increased the per customer limit to eight tins per customer.&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\nRestrictions have been enforced on baby formula purchases since 2015 due to the increase in demand fuelled by shoppers (known as daigou) buying tins in bulk and selling them to parents in China.<br />\n<br />\nMany Chinese parents have not trusted their own country's milk formula since a tragic melamine contamination killed six babies and hospitalised thousands more in 2008.<br />\n<br />\nChan and his fellow signees have requested Woolworths reduce their limit to two tins per customer &quot;to ensure adequate supply for Australian families&quot;.<br />\n<br />\nIn a response to Chan's Facebook post, Woolworths said it would consider making a change to the limit.<br />\n<br />\n&quot;We've been working very closely with our suppliers and recently changed our formula tin limit as a result of improving supply in the market,&quot; the comment read.<br />\n<br />\n&quot;We will continue to carefully monitor stock availability, supply arrangements and feedback from customers and will adjust the limit again if needed.&quot;<br />\n<br />\nWoolworths reiterated the statement when contacted for comment.<br />\n<br />\nCorrection: An earlier version of this story said that Coles had an eight-tin limit. Coles, in fact, has a limit of two tins per customer per purchase.<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.mamamia.com.au/baby-formula-limit/\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mamamia.com.au%2Fbaby-formula-limit%2F&d=XAwIn4HCiavbvNoE0BIO3jOU%2Fspzl0GStOx2So8CiJ8%3D&h=0817bba5\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.mamamia.com.au/baby-formula-limit/</a>"},{"pid":"e7c2d33a95897e0b0c33267331762ce3412538ad","tid":871032,"uid":79563,"like":9,"dislike":617,"score":-608,"citedBy":4,"replyTime":"2018-10-21T15:13:39.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"http://dadazim.com/journal/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/beast.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=http%3A%2F%2Fdadazim.com%2Fjournal%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2013%2F01%2Fbeast.jpg&h=da23c811&s={SIZE}\" />"},{"pid":"fa9a80f18db340db53ebe9775ea1477984da6757","tid":871032,"uid":4964,"like":325,"dislike":0,"score":325,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2018-10-21T15:14:23.000Z","msg":"當年西媒話我地歧視，係時候感受下"},{"pid":"67d5a35c972ed38e15140f5ca8c4b0b45d19cedf","tid":871032,"uid":152476,"like":343,"dislike":2,"score":341,"quote":{"pid":"e7c2d33a95897e0b0c33267331762ce3412538ad","tid":871032,"uid":79563,"like":9,"dislike":617,"score":-608,"citedBy":4,"replyTime":"2018-10-21T15:13:39.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"http://dadazim.com/journal/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/beast.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=http%3A%2F%2Fdadazim.com%2Fjournal%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2013%2F01%2Fbeast.jpg&h=da23c811&s={SIZE}\" />"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2018-10-21T15:14:50.000Z","msg":"屌佢老味<br />\n中國人出現之前根本唔使搶<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/clown.gif\" c